headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 38 points and the Atlanta Hawks beat the depleted Los Angeles Clippers 108-99 on Tuesday night, ending the Clippers’ seven-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 38 points lead Hawks past depleted Clippers, 108-99

headlines.description: — John Wall scored 24 points in his first game against his former team, leading the Houston Rockets to a 107-88 victory over the Washington Wizards on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wall scores 24 to lead Rockets over Wizards 107-88

events.name: New York Knicks at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 18 points, 19 rebounds and four blocked shots, and the Utah Jazz beat the New York Knicks 108-94 on Tuesday night for their ninth consecutive win.
